message:
Update README.md (#16)

Add codeclimate badges and fix markdown issues.
Add GitHub Actions badge to README.md (#201)

Offer alternative solution for Auxmoney (#202)

I tried to write a configuration for this project to handle Auxmoney exports. Unfortunately, that is not possible in a meaningful way. Therefore, I created a separate project to handle this and would like to offer your audience to use this as well.

Co-authored-by: ChrisRBe <31167512+ChrisRBe@users.noreply.github.com>
add initial support for debitum network

Add support for viainvest

This adds support for parsing viainvest account statements. Withdrawals are currently not supported, only deposits and interest payments.

README.md: update readme wrt installation

Add preference to using pipenv over plain pip.

README: fix header alignment

use align="center" instead of style

README: beautify readme files

center heading and badges. Add example heading from #541

README: change format on section

Add information section to make it better visible

github.yaml: update python version in build matrix

update build matrix to drop support for python 3.7 and add
support for 3.11 and 3.12

readme.md: remove python 3.12

3.12 only available as alpha version right now.

pipenv(chore): split requirements.txt file

Previously, requirements.txt file included everything, even dependencies
from top level packages. Using newer pipenv version gives the
requirements subcommand to create matching requirements.txt files.
This change also introduces separate requirements.txt files for
production and one for development purposes. This way only the
necessary packages are installed when you only want to use it.
This change should hopefully also improve the maintenance effort on
dependabot side.
